A GOGO and her two grandchildren have survived hostage drama in Umbumbulu, Durban, following the arrest of two suspects. Police are still chasing the remaining three suspects. It alleged that five suspects were involved in a business robbery in Cato Ridge, outside Durban, earlier on Tuesday, 1 February. And when a cop arrived on the scene, they fled the scene and headed toward Umbumbulu, then split once they entered the semi-rural area. One suspect then went into a house and held a family hostage, but specialist negotiators were able to convince him to release the family without any harm. Brigadier Jay Naicker said it was alleged that a business robbery occurred at 10.30am when the men entered a cellphone shop and robbed the staff at gunpoint. “The suspects stole a large number of cellphones before fleeing the scene in a getaway vehicle. Magma Security was contacted and responded before alerting the police,” said Naicker. He said the suspects fled towards Umbumbulu. HAPPENING NOW: Hostage situation in uMbumbulu south of Durban.A robbery suspect who was on the run from police gained entry into this house and is holding the family hostage. The suspect is armed.#sabcnews pic.twitter.com/0qbF5RQsHg  “On a dirt road, they lost control of their vehicle. They alighted while firing shots at the officers. One of them was arrested while others ran into the bushes. Officers from the K9 unit and special task force also joined in on the chase. One suspect fled into a nearby house and held the occupants hostage,” he said. Naicker said after a lengthy standoff, with the assistance of hostage negotiators, the suspect was apprehended and his firearm seized. “The grandmother and her two grandchildren were released unharmed. Three other suspects are still being pursued by the police,” said Naicker.